==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irreligious
<hw>Ir`re*li"gious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>irreligiosus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>irr⟦eacute⟧ligieux</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of religion; not controlled by religious
motives or principles; ungodly. Cf. <er>Impious</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shame and reproach are generally the portion of the impious and
<qex>irreligious</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indicating a lack of religion; profane; wicked;
<as>as, <ex>irreligious</ex> speech</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irreligiously</ent>⟦br⟧
